Latvia May Lift Property Tax in 2012 Budget, Latvijas Avize Says

-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 
2011-02-18T07:19:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/latvia-may-lift-property-tax-in-2012-budget-latvijas-avize-says.html
  Latvia  may raise its real-estate tax
to bring in more revenue in its 2012 budget, said Finance
Minister Andris Vilks, according to  Latvijas Avize .  It would be the only tax raised and the country should
consider lowering its income tax rates to levels in Estonia and  Lithuania  in the future, Vilks said, according to the Latvian
language newspaper.  Vilks said the state revenue service has signed cooperation
agreements with 11 business associations to enhance compliance
with paying taxes, according to Latvijas Avize.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor for this story:
